                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New York, Oct. 26: Billionaire investor Warren Buffett has made a surprise move by hiring a little-known hedge fund manager Todd Combs to manage a significant part of Berkshire Hathaways investments. Combs, who has been managing Castle Point Capital for the past five years as chief executive and portfolio manager, will soon join Berkshire as an investment manager and oversee a part of the $100-billion investment portfolio.                             
	 Mumbai, Oct. 26: The Reserve Bank of India today hinted at another round of monetary policy tightening at its upcoming review meet on November 2, with deputy governor Subir Gokarn asserting that it is a challenge to keep inflation in check.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 26: Tata Steel has formed a joint venture with Canadian entity New Millennium Capital Corp for iron ore mining operations in Canada. The move will help the steel maker boost raw material supply.
                                                                                                                          
